Modifications in this port
--------------------------
No changes to the KNN algorithm. Build-only changes to support AMD ROCm/HIP
(gfx1100/1101/1102/1151/1200/1201), all guarded with `#ifndef __HIP_PLATFORM_AMD__`
so CUDA builds remain identical:
  * guard out the CUDA-only header device_launch_parameters.h on ROCm;
  * drop the unused cooperative_groups dependency (ROCm lacks
    cooperative_groups/reduce.h), using the plain 1-D global thread index;
  * normalise spaced kernel-launch chevrons ("<< <" / ">> >") so hipify converts
    them.
cub -> hipCUB and thrust -> rocThrust are handled by PyTorch's hipify.
